\pard\b\fs30 13 Test and Acceptance Criteria\b0\fs22\par
\pard\sa120 Numerical decoding must show that remainder_offset calculations match the adjacent-representable reference behaviour.\par
\pard\sa120 Forward equivalence must show that width zero and zero-code active mode reproduce the base model.\par
\pard\sa120 Addressing tests must show that a single remainder code mutation affects exactly one intended matrix coordinate.\par
\pard\sa120 Projection tests must show that grad_effective reconstructs as grad_projected plus grad_remainder within tolerance.\par
\pard\sa120 R1 PoC training must improve a controlled objective and short language-model run if the idea has signal.\par
\pard\sa120 R2 target optimiser tests must show bounded integer updates and no dense per-weight FP persistent state.\par
\pard\sa120 DDP tests must show two-rank rank agreement, exact resume behaviour, and atomic skip semantics.\par

\pard\b\fs30 14 Deferred Work and Risks\b0\fs22\par
\pard\sa120 If R1 PoC training fails at four bits, stop before R2 and packed-storage work.\par
\pard\sa120 If R1 works but R2 fails, revise the optimiser rather than immediately adding dense state.\par
\pard\sa120 If DDP ranks diverge, block release until rank-consistency tests pass.\par
\pard\sa120 If saturation is high, inspect grad_remainder and bit width before increasing update size.\par
\pard\sa120 If peak memory rises too much, use streamed backward only after scientific value is established.\par

\pard\b\fs30 15 Controlled Terminology\b0\fs22\par
\pard\sa120 Approved: remainder code. Avoid: correction code.\par
\pard\sa120 Approved: remainder_offset. Avoid: decoded value when the offset is meant.\par
\pard\sa120 Approved: effective_weight. Avoid: effective value.\par
\pard\sa120 Approved: remainder-enabled. Avoid: covered.\par
\pard\sa120 Approved: gradient_projector. Avoid: projector before it has been defined.\par
\pard\sa120 Approved: grad_effective, grad_projected, grad_remainder. Avoid: G_effective, G_projected, G_remainder.\par
\pard\sa120 Approved: R1 PoC training. Avoid: reference training.\par
\pard\qc\i\sa160 End of Requirements Specification v0.14.\i0\par
